    wow: `In the myth of the Argonauts, {nombre} tends to be that crew member who studies the stars and the maps before the ship sets sail. Their nature seems to be that of intelligent preparation. You will likely notice that {nombre} tends to value instructions deeply. Their contribution to the crew tends to be quality in execution — they do not seem to seek to be the fastest or the loudest, but the most precise. Their value tends to lie in their ability to follow the game plan with a faithfulness that brings order to the whole team. Their great strength tends to be attention to detail: the ability to notice those small technical adjustments that take a play from "good" to "perfect."`,
    motorDesc: `{nombre}'s profile is associated with a naturally balanced rhythm. This suggests their system prefers to process information before activating a physical response. A closer look: Sport is likely a challenge to be solved correctly. They do not "kick the ball" just to kick it — their mind tends to evaluate the position, the force, and the direction. If they sometimes seem to take an extra instant, it is likely not doubt, but calibration. Once their balanced rhythm processes an instruction and finds it logical, their execution tends to be among the cleanest in the group. Attunement invitation: Give them time to "digest" a new tactic. After watching the drill a couple of times, they will likely carry it out with a precision that surprises everyone.`,
    combustible: `{nombre}'s fuel tends to be technical competence and clarity. They likely feel most alive when they understand the "why" of things and when they manage to execute a movement exactly as it was explained. They are motivated by mastery of technique. Attunement feedback: They tend to thrive on specific feedback. Instead of "Well done!", try: "I noticed how you positioned your foot for that pass — it was technically perfect." This validates their mental process and their effort toward precision.`,
    grupoEspacio: `On the team: They tend to connect through shared task work. They tend to respect teammates who make an effort to play well and who honor agreements. They do not typically seek emotional leadership, but tend to be a tactical reference for others: "if you want to know how this drill is done, watch {nombre}." In the space: They tend to feel comfortable in structured environments. They like knowing the boundaries of the field and their exact position. Disorder or trainings where "anything goes" can generate an invisible mental fatigue because their mind tends to try to find an order where there is none.`,
    corazon: `To connect with {nombre}, it is valuable to understand what lies behind their seriousness. What it may look like: They can sometimes give the impression of being meticulous, serious, or choosing carefully before acting. What it likely is (The Intention): A desire not to let the team down. {nombre} tends to take the game with responsibility because they feel their precision is their way of helping. Their "meticulousness" tends to actually be concentration and respect for the sport. Emotional barometer: Their frustration tends to be internal and technical. If they are unable to execute a movement the way they know it should be done, they may become quieter than usual, taking internal time to process what happened in detail. They tend to be more bothered by technical misalignment than by the result on the scoreboard.`,
    palabrasPuente: [`Technique`, `Precision`, `Plan`, `Logic`, `Adjust`, `How`],
    palabrasRuido: [`Whatever comes out`, `Don't plan`, `Don't think`, `Just improvise`, `Forget the technique`],
